	abstract = {Taiwan is aimed towards building a favorable environment for the development of the cultural and creative industries and in this direction the Republic of China government officially designated cultural and creative industries in 2002 as part of the Challenge 2008 National Development Plan. As these industries came under the purview of different government agencies, an inter-ministerial team under the Ministry of Economic Affairs (MOEA) was established with the aim of coordinating the efforts of government agencies involved in the task of developing cultural and creative industries. The First Cultural and Creative Industries Roundtable Forum aimed at promoting investment in the cultural and creative industries, and toward deepening the islands cultural depth through education. The Creative Taiwan project identifies television, design, handicrafts and industrial artworks, films, pop music and digital content as the six flagship cultural creative industries.},
